# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Documented ignores for Trivy HIGH/CRITICAL scan.
# Each entry explains WHY it cannot be fixed within the current Spring Boot
# 3.3.x line and what upgrade path will remove it.
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# CVE-2026-35554 — kafka-clients 3.7.1 information-disclosure (HIGH).
# Fixed in 3.9.2+, but bumping kafka-clients breaks spring-kafka-test's
# EmbeddedKafka (KafkaConfig.scala expects kafka-server 3.7.x APIs from the
# Spring Boot 3.3.x BOM). Remove once project upgrades to Spring Boot 3.4+.
CVE-2026-35554

# CVE-2026-22732 — spring-security-web (CRITICAL, Spring Security 6.3.x).
# Fixed in 6.5.9 / 7.0.4 only; the 6.3.x branch is EOL and will not receive a
# patch. Requires upgrading to Spring Boot 3.5+ which ships Spring Security
# 6.5.x. Remove alongside the Boot 3.5 upgrade.
CVE-2026-22732

# CVE-2025-41249 — spring-core (HIGH, Spring Framework 6.1.x).
# Fixed in 6.2.11; Spring Boot 3.3.x stays on Spring Framework 6.1.x.
# Requires upgrading to Spring Boot 3.4+ (ships Framework 6.2.x).
CVE-2025-41249

# CVE-2026-29129 — tomcat-embed-core (HIGH, cipher preference).
# As of 2026-04 no fixed version is published upstream; Trivy marks the row
# with no "Fixed Version". Will be removed once Apache Tomcat publishes a fix
# and the Spring Boot BOM picks it up.
CVE-2026-29129

# CVE-2025-12183 — lz4-java 1.8.0 out-of-bounds (HIGH).
# Fix version 1.8.1 advertised by the advisory but not yet published on
# Maven Central under org.lz4:lz4-java (latest available GA is 1.8.0).
# Pulled transitively via kafka-clients. Remove once 1.8.1 is released.
CVE-2025-12183
